dc_description_s: Map shows the Cameroons under the British administration were divided by a strech of approximately 45 miles into north and south by the Benue River. Map shows area administered: as Cameroons Province, by the Residents of Bornu, Yola, and Muri provinces. Map shows Nigeria-Cameroons, Anglo-French and provincial boundaries, province and divisional headquarters, roads, railways, courts, preventive stations, mission stations, and schools. Original map is filed in the Map/Geospatial Center, map reproduction is attached to companion volume. "R. O,1007" ; "P.2728,8471.A-2265/625,875,8/29"
